    <section>
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>Assorted vegetables (zucchini, sweet potatoes, bell peppers, etc.)</li>
            <li>Seafood (shrimp, fish fillets, squid, etc.)</li>
            <li>1 cup all-purpose flour</li>
            <li>1 cup ice-cold water</li>
            <li>1 egg, beaten</li>
            <li>Ice cubes</li>
            <li>Vegetable oil, for frying</li>
            <li>Soy sauce, for dipping</li>
            <li>Tempura dipping sauce (tentsuyu), optional</li>
        </ul>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Tags</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Tempura</li>
            <li>Japanese</li>
            <li>Fried</li>
            <li>Seafood</li>
            <li>Vegetables</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

    <section>
        <h2>Instructions</h2>
        <ol>
            <li>Prepare the vegetables and seafood by cutting them into bite-sized pieces.</li>
            <li>In a large bowl, mix flour, ice-cold water, beaten egg, and ice cubes. Stir until the batter is just combined. It's okay if there are lumps.</li>
            <li>Heat vegetable oil in a deep fryer or large pot to 350°F (180°C).</li>
            <li>Dip the vegetables and seafood into the tempura batter, coating them evenly.</li>
            <li>Carefully place the coated pieces into the hot oil and fry until golden brown and crispy. Work in batches to avoid overcrowding the fryer.</li>
            <li>Remove the tempura with a slotted spoon and place them on a plate lined with paper towels to drain excess oil.</li>
            <li>Serve the tempura hot with soy sauce for dipping. Optionally, serve with tempura dipping sauce (tentsuyu).</li>
            <li>Enjoy your delicious homemade Tempura!</li>
        </ol>
    </section>

